         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
               <PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
                  <D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                     <D_TECHNICAL/>
                  </D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>“The Vehicle Support Team - Armoured Tracks Portfolio, part of the Ministry of Defence, intends to place an 18 month supply contract with BAE Systems Global Combat Systems Ltd. (“the Contractor”) for the Procurement of Capital Spares to Support the Availability of Titan and Trojan:</P>
                     <P>— qty 2 NSN: 6220-99-667-6416 Headlight,</P>
                     <P>— qty 4 NSN: 2590-99-757-4934 Titan Launch Pads,</P>
                     <P>— qty 4 NSN: 6220-99737-3214 Light Unit,</P>
                     <P>— qty 2 NSN: 4730-99-613-1817 Bridging Filter Assembly, and,</P>
                     <P>— qty 2 NSN: 4810-99-273-8078 Valve Assembly.</P>
                     <P>It is considered that this Contract can be placed using the Negotiated Procedure Without Prior Publication of a Contract Notice, pursuant to Articles 28(1)(e) and 28(3)(a) of Directive 2009/81/EC (Regulations 16(1)(a)(ii) and 16(1)(b)(i)(aa) of the UK Defence and Security Public Contract Regulations 2011 respectively) for technical reasons and to procure the replacement spares would result in incompatibility between the Titan and Trojan platforms and the spares and potential difficulties in the operation and maintenance of the platforms.</P>
                     <P>Only the Contractor, as the Design Authority and Original Equipment Manufacturer for the Titan and Trojan platforms, has access to the design and technical information, expertise, knowledge, and know-how necessary to provide the required goods. A 3rd party would not be able to carry out this work without access to the necessary design and technical information which is required to produce the goods to the correct technical specification, in terms of quality, performance, and safety.</P>
                     <P>The goods being procured under this contract have been deemed to be safety critical to the operation of the platform and so the goods must be produced to the correct specification, held only by BAE Systems. This information is not available to the Authority as it is owned by the Contractor in their role as the Design Authority and the Authority does not have the necessary rights to that information to provide to any 3rd party.</P>
                     <P>There is also a strict technical impracticality for a supplier other than the Contractor to fulfil the activity associated with updating and approval of the Platform Safety Case within the required timescales, and to the necessary standard and to the reasonable satisfaction of the Authority.".</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
            </DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
